This paper deals with Byzantine agreement protocols, which are a fundamental building block in distributed systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also relies on cryptographic assumptions and public key infrastructure, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper deals with communication complexity, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
